<p>

<b><it>Music from 'Cal</it></b><it> is an album of music composed by <person wordnetid="100007846" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<artist wordnetid="109812338" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../158/199158.xml">
Mark Knopfler</link></artist>
</person>
 for the 1984 film </it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../183/7352183.xml">
Cal</link></movie>
<it>, produced by <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../492/417492.xml">
David Putnam</link>, who also produced the film <movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../104/242104.xml">
Local Hero</link></movie>
 with its best selling Knopfler <album wordnetid="106591815" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../024/3564024.xml">
soundtrack</link></album>
. Title of the album is "music from" rather than "soundtrack", which in this context is a euphemism for the tracks having being edited to give a more coherent music album, rather than just the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../319/55319.xml">
ambient music</link> used within the context of the movie, and unlike many soundtracks, works well even if you've never seen the film.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref></it></p>
